==English==

=== Pronunciation ===
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /'/
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /'bɑʊnd/

===Verb===

'''bound'''

# Past tense of [[bind]].
#: ''I bound the splint to my leg.''
# Past participle of to [[bind]]
#: ''I had bound the splint with duct tape.''
# To surround a territory.
#: ''Nebraska, Missouri, Oklahoma and Colorado bound Kansas.''

====Usage note====
The bordering sense of ''bound'' tends to be used in passive voice, as ''Kansas is bounded by Nebraska on the north, Missouri on the east ...''.

